<p>
    I am an Assistant Professor at the <a href="https://www.dcu.ie/computing">School of Computing</a> in <a href="https://www.dcu.ie/">Dublin City University</a>. My research interests include application of semantics towards solving real-world challenges associated with privacy, data protection, legal and regulatory compliance, and consent. My PhD (Computer Science, Trinity College Dublin) explored the application of linked data and semantic web technologies towards GDPR compliance, with a particular focus on consent and provenance. I chair the W3C Data Privacy Vocabularies and Controls Community Group (DPVCG) â€“ which develops interoperable vocabularies for privacy and data protection activities based on legal and practical requirements. I am also involved in international standardisation activities through the National Standards Authority of Ireland and the <a href="https://www.iso.org/committee/45306.html">ISO/IEC JTC1/SC27</a> subcommittee on cybersecurity and privacy protection. 
